Ira Lubert is a founding Partner of LBC Credit Partners, which, together with Lubert-Adler Real Estate, LLR Partners, Inc., Quaker Partners, LEM Mezzanine, Inc., and Patriot Financial Partners, L.P. constitute Independence Capital Partners, a family of private equity and real estate funds, all of which he co-founded. He has over 35 years of experience in the real estate and private equity sectors.
Previous Experience

Principal and founder of TL Ventures, within the family of Safeguard Scientifics, Inc. (NYSE: SFE), an early-stage venture fund.


Founder of Radnor Venture Partners, L.P., the first venture fund managed by Safeguard Scientifics.


Chairman of the Board and President of CompuCom Systems, a microcomputer reseller with $2 billion in annual revenues.


